        <div class="khoj-desc">
            <p>The Khoj function is an integral part of Monad's curriculum and is designed to encourage students to explore their interests and passions. The function is held annually and is a platform for students to showcase their talents in various areas, including sports, music, dance, art, and drama. It provides an opportunity for students to express themselves and develop their skills while building confidence and self-esteem.</p>
            <p>The Khoj function is not just limited to academic pursuits but also focuses on developing life skills such as teamwork, leadership, and communication. The event includes a range of activities that promote collaboration and cooperation among students. For instance, students are encouraged to work in groups to plan and organize events such as stage performances, exhibitions, and sports competitions.</p>
            <p>Moreover, the Khoj function encourages students to be environmentally responsible and aware. As part of the event, Monad Public School organizes various workshops and seminars on sustainable living and environmental conservation. This initiative helps to instill a sense of responsibility and concern for the environment among students.</p>
            <p>The Khoj function is an excellent opportunity for parents and teachers to see the progress and growth of their children. It provides a platform for students to showcase their skills and talents, which in turn boosts their confidence and self-esteem. It also allows parents to interact with teachers and gain insight into their child's learning and development.</p>
            <p>In conclusion, Monad Public School's Khoj function is a unique and innovative approach to learning that encourages students to explore their interests, develop their skills, and build their self-confidence. It is a testament to the school's commitment to providing a holistic and well-rounded education to its students. If you are looking for a school that focuses on your child's overall development, Monad Public School is the place to be.</p>
